Doublets

suppressMessages(library(SingleCellExperiment))
suppressMessages(library(scDblFinder))
suppressMessages(library(ggplot2))
sce <- readRDS("/mnt/nmorais-nfs/marta/pA_karine/r_session/e12h-preliminary-analysis/integration/data/sce-raw.rds")
sample <- as.character(sce$sample)
doublets <- scDblFinder(sce = as.matrix(counts(sce)), samples = sample)
## Assuming the input to be a matrix of counts or expected counts.
scores <- doublets$scDblFinder.score
hist(scores, main="Distribution of Doublet Scores", xlab="Doublet Score")

lib <- colSums(counts(sce))
feat <- counts(sce) > 0 
feat <- colSums(feat)
df_qc <- data.frame(library_size = log10(lib),
                    total_features = log10(feat),
                    doublets_score = scores,
                    sample = sce$sample)
  df_qc <- df_qc[order(df_qc$doublets_score, decreasing = FALSE),]
  print(colnames(df_qc))
## [1] "library_size"   "total_features" "doublets_score" "sample"
ggplot(data = df_qc, aes(x = library_size, 
                                y = total_features, 
                                color = doublets_score)) + 
    geom_point( size = 0.3, alpha = 1) + 
    scale_color_gradient2(midpoint = 0.5, low = "darkgreen", mid = "yellow", high="red") + 
    xlab("log10(Library size)") +
    ylab("log10(Total features)") +
    labs(color = "Doublet score") +
    theme(text = element_text(size=20), 
          panel.grid.major = element_blank(), panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
          panel.background = element_blank(), axis.line = element_line(colour = "black")) +  


   facet_wrap(~ df_qc[["sample"]])

  df_qc <- df_qc[order(df_qc$doublets_score, decreasing = FALSE),]
  print(colnames(df_qc))
## [1] "library_size"   "total_features" "doublets_score" "sample"
  df_qc <- df_qc[df_qc$doublets_score > 0.99,]
  
ggplot(data = df_qc, aes(x = library_size, 
                                y = total_features, 
                                color = doublets_score)) + 
    geom_point( size = 0.3, alpha = 1) + 
    scale_color_gradient2(midpoint = 0.5, low = "darkgreen", mid = "yellow", high="red") + 
    xlab("log10(Library size)") +
    ylab("log10(Total features)") +
    labs(color = "Doublet score") +
    theme(text = element_text(size=20), 
          panel.grid.major = element_blank(), panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
          panel.background = element_blank(), axis.line = element_line(colour = "black")) +  


   facet_wrap(~ df_qc[["sample"]])

doublet_class <- scores > 0.99
